race.comment: FAVOUR THE BOLD (1) went close here on debut and resumes owning a trial win at the track. Has the early speed to manage the awkward barrier and he will be naturally improved. The one they have to beat. SATIN'S LEGACY (10) resumes and has switched from a top Sydney stable on a 299-day return. Had excuses in town on debut and will be fitter for two provincial trials. Morgan sticks from the latest and a bold run is likely. HARAS (8) debuts and looked good beaten a nose here in a recent trial. Has the rail and Reith and she also looks set to race well. SCARLET MONARCH (11) has race fitness and may be the best of the rest.
